\section1 Table and Tree View

\section2 TableViewDelegate

A standard delegate for table views.

\table
\row
    \li \b{Type}
    \li{2, 1} TableViewDelegate

\row
    \li{1, 6} \b{States}
    \li{2, 1} Hovered
\row
    \li{2, 1} ActiveFocus
\row
    \li{2, 1} VisualFocus
\row
    \li{2, 1} Pressed
\row
    \li{2, 1} Enabled
\row
    \li{2, 1} Highlighted

\row
    \li{1, 4} \b{Hints}
    \li \b alternating-colors
    \li Set when the delegate should be using alternating row colors.
\row
    \li \b editing
    \li Set when the user is currently editing the table cell.
\row
    \li \b current
    \li Set when the table cell is the currently selected cell.
\row
    \li \b selected
    \li Set when the table cell is in the selected set of cells.


\endtable

\section3 Sub-Elements

\section4 Text

The text displayed by the button. Style it using the text related
properties.




\section4 EditDelegate

A text field that is used when the user is editing the table cell.






\section2 TreeViewDelegate

A standard delegate for tree views.

\table
\row
    \li \b{Type}
    \li{2, 1} TreeViewDelegate

\row
    \li{1, 6} \b{States}
    \li{2, 1} Hovered
\row
    \li{2, 1} ActiveFocus
\row
    \li{2, 1} VisualFocus
\row
    \li{2, 1} Pressed
\row
    \li{2, 1} Enabled
\row
    \li{2, 1} Highlighted

\row
    \li{1, 5} \b{Hints}
    \li \b alternating-colors
    \li Set when the delegate should be using alternating row colors.
\row
    \li \b expanded
    \li Set when the children of the tree node are visible.
\row
    \li \b editing
    \li Set when the user is currently editing the table cell.
\row
    \li \b current
    \li Set when the tree cell is the currently selected cell.
\row
    \li \b selected
    \li Set when the tree cell is in the selected set of cells.


\endtable

\section3 Sub-Elements

\section4 Icon

The icon displayed by the element. Style it using the icon related
properties.




\section4 Text

The text displayed by the button. Style it using the text related
properties.




\section4 Indentation

A transparent item used to reserve space for tree indentation. This
should be placed at the start of the delegate.


\table
\row
    \li \b{Type}
    \li{2, 1} Indentation




\endtable


\section4 Indicator

An icon used to indicate the tree node has children. Usually styled
as an arrow.


\table
\row
    \li \b{Type}
    \li{2, 1} Indicator




\endtable


\section4 EditDelegate

A text field that is used when the user is editing the tree cell.





\section1 Table and Tree Views

\section2 Header View

A horizontal or vertical view of table headers.

\table
\row
    \li \b{Type}
    \li{2, 1} HeaderView

\row
    \li{1, 2} \b{States}
    \li{2, 1} ActiveFocus
\row
    \li{2, 1} Enabled

\row
    \li{1, 2} \b{Hints}
    \li \b horizontal
    \li Set when the header view is oriented horizontally.
\row
    \li \b vertical
    \li Set when the header view is oriented vertically.


\endtable

\section3 Sub-Elements

\section4 Delegate

An element used to show a single entry of the view.

\table
\row
    \li \b{Type}
    \li{2, 1} HeaderViewDelegate

\row
    \li{1, 2} \b{States}
    \li{2, 1} ActiveFocus
\row
    \li{2, 1} Enabled

\row
    \li{1, 4} \b{Hints}
    \li \b horizontal
    \li Set when the delegate is used for a horizontally oriented header view.
\row
    \li \b vertical
    \li Set when the delegate is used for a vertically oriented header view.
\row
    \li \b sort-ascending
    \li Set when the delegate should indicate ascending sorting is
active for the associated table or tree column.

\row
    \li \b sort-descending
    \li Set when the delegate should indicate descending sorting is
active for the associated table or tree column.



\endtable

\section3 Sub-Elements

\section4 Icon

An icon that can be used to display sorting state.



\section4 Text

A text element that shows the row or column's title.






\section2 HeaderViewDelegate

A standard delegate that can be used in a header view.

\note This is separate from the HeaderView delegate because of Qt
versioning reasons.


\table
\row
    \li \b{Type}
    \li{2, 1} HeaderViewDelegate

\row
    \li{1, 6} \b{States}
    \li{2, 1} Hovered
\row
    \li{2, 1} ActiveFocus
\row
    \li{2, 1} VisualFocus
\row
    \li{2, 1} Pressed
\row
    \li{2, 1} Enabled
\row
    \li{2, 1} Highlighted

\row
    \li{1, 2} \b{Hints}
    \li \b horizontal
    \li Set when the delegate is intended for a horizontal header.
\row
    \li \b vertical
    \li Set when the delegate is intended for a vertical header.


\endtable

\section3 Sub-Elements

\section4 Text

The text that should be displayed.





