\section2 Application Header

Base type for Kirigami's application headers.

\table
\row
    \li \b{Type}
    \li{2, 1} ApplicationHeader


\row
    \li{1, 1} \b{Hints}
    \li \b with-separator
    \li Set when the header should show a separator below it.


\endtable



\section2 Card

An element grouping together information in a view.

\table
\row
    \li \b{Type}
    \li{2, 1} Card

\row
    \li{1, 7} \b{States}
    \li{2, 1} Hovered
\row
    \li{2, 1} ActiveFocus
\row
    \li{2, 1} VisualFocus
\row
    \li{2, 1} Pressed
\row
    \li{2, 1} Checked
\row
    \li{2, 1} Enabled
\row
    \li{2, 1} Highlighted



\endtable



\section2 Chip

A small element used to show tags or similar information.

\table
\row
    \li \b{Type}
    \li{2, 1} Chip

\row
    \li{1, 6} \b{States}
    \li{2, 1} Hovered
\row
    \li{2, 1} ActiveFocus
\row
    \li{2, 1} VisualFocus
\row
    \li{2, 1} Pressed
\row
    \li{2, 1} Checked
\row
    \li{2, 1} Enabled

\row
    \li{1, 2} \b{Hints}
    \li \b closable
    \li Set when the chip should show a button to remove it.
\row
    \li \b interactive
    \li Set when the chip can be interacted with.

\row
    \li{1, 1} \b{Attributes}
        \li \b display
    \li A hint indicating what sub-controls should be visible. \br
        Possible values:
        \list
            \li \b icon-only Only display the icon.
            \li \b text-only Only display the text.
            \li \b text-beside-icon Display both icon and text in a row.
            \li \b text-below-icon Display both icon and text with the text below the icon.
        \endlist


\endtable

\section3 Sub-Elements

\section4 Icon

The icon displayed by the chip. Style it using the icon related
properties.




\section4 Text

The text displayed by the chip. Style it using the text related
properties.




\section4 Indicator

A toolbutton used for removing or other actions on the chip.


\table
\row
    \li \b{Type}
    \li{2, 1} ToolButton


\row
    \li{1, 1} \b{Hints}
    \li \b indicator
    \li Used to indicate this is an indicator toolbutton.


\endtable




\section2 Heading

A text element that is used as a title for a different section of content.

\table
\row
    \li \b{Type}
    \li{2, 1} Heading


\row
    \li{1, 3} \b{Hints}
    \li \b level-{1-6}
    \li The level of the heading. Lower levels mean bigger headings.
\row
    \li \b primary
    \li Set when the heading should be shown emphasized as a primary heading.
\row
    \li \b secondary
    \li Set when the heading should be shown deemphasized as a secondary heading.


\endtable



\section2 InlineMessage

A text with a distinct background used to display messages to the user.

\table
\row
    \li \b{Type}
    \li{2, 1} InlineMessage



\row
    \li{1, 2} \b{Attributes}
        \li \b type
    \li The type of message. \br
        Possible values:
        \list
            \li \b positive The message shows something succeeded or similarly positive.
            \li \b warning The message gives a warning that something is wrong.
            \li \b error The message shows an error.
        \endlist

\row
        \li \b position
    \li Where the message is located relative to content. \br
        Possible values:
        \list
            \li \b inline The message is shown inline with the content.
            \li \b header The message is shown as a header on top of the content.
            \li \b footer The message is shown as a footer below the content.
        \endlist


\endtable



\section2 NavigationTabBar

A tab bar used for navigating between different pages of an application.

